  <!-- EN: Xuan turtle -->
  <RI_Animal_XuanTurtle.label>旋龟</RI_Animal_XuanTurtle.label>
  <!-- EN: “The Xuan turtle resembles a tortoise, yet bears the head of a bird and the tail of a viper. Its name is Xuan turtle; its sounds like wood being split. Wearing it wards off deafness, and it may also serve as a foundation.”\n\nXuan turtles favor quiet stretches of forest streams and still waters. Far more aggressive than ordinary turtles, their sharp, curved beaks can easily tear flesh, while their powerful limbs allow them to traverse rugged terrain and even climb rock faces. Xuan turtles are averse to heat; during summer, their flattened bodies slip into crevices between streambed stones to escape the high temperatures. -->
  <RI_Animal_XuanTurtle.description>玄龟，其状如龟而鸟首虺尾，其名曰旋龟，其音如判木，佩之不聋，可以为底。\n\n旋龟喜欢生活在森林溪流静水区域。比起寻常龟类，它们更有攻击性，尖锐弯曲的喙部可以轻松撕开皮肉，粗壮的四肢让它们能够跋山涉水，甚至是攀爬岩壁。旋龟害怕炎热，在夏季，旋龟扁平的身子可以藏在溪流石缝中躲避高温。</RI_Animal_XuanTurtle.description>
  <!-- EN: beak -->
  <RI_Animal_XuanTurtle.tools.beak.label>喙</RI_Animal_XuanTurtle.tools.beak.label>
  
  <!-- EN: Xuan turtle egg (fert.) -->
  <RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleFertilized.label>旋龟蛋（已受精）</RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleFertilized.label>
  <!-- EN: A fertilized Xuan turtle egg. If all goes well, it should hatch into a baby Xuan turtle. -->
  <RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleFertilized.description>一枚受精的旋龟蛋。如果一切顺利，它应该会孵化出一只旋龟宝宝。</RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleFertilized.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Xuan turtle (unfert.) -->
  <RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleUnfertilized.label>旋龟蛋（未受精）</RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleUnfertilized.label>
  <!-- EN: An unfertilized Xuan turtle egg. -->
  <RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleUnfertilized.description>一枚未受精的旋龟蛋。</RI_Thing_EggXuanTurtleUnfertilized.description>
  
</LanguageData>